==English==

===Verb===
'''[[beat]] [[up]]'''
# To give a [[beating]] to
#:''I got beaten up by thugs on my way home''
# ''([[Intransitive]], nautical):'' To [[sail]] to [[windward]] using a [[series]] of [[alternate]] [[tack]]s across the [[wind]].


And [[metaphorical]] [[reflexive]] use: "to beat oneself up over the matter X" = "to feel badly guilty and accuse oneself over the matter X".

